            any historically detected features. For such functionality please use the Hybrid version of apLCMS.

            @GENERAL_HELP@

This is the **Two-Step Hybrid** version of **apLCMS**. This tool is improved upon the Hybrid version by accounting for the batch effects in multi-batch experiments. As in the Hybrid version, this tool incorporates the knowledge of known metabolites and historically detected features on the same machinery to help detect and quantify lower-intensity peaks.
**CAUTION**: To use such knowledge, especially historical data, you must keep using (1) the same chromatography system (otherwise the retention time will not match), and (2) the same type of samples with similar extraction technique, such as human serum.
@GENERAL_HELP@
